definitions.definition: Later ; second (of two); next , following , subsequent
At or towards the stern of a ship or the rear of an aircraft.
examples: The after gun is mounted aft.
The after gun is abaft the forward gun.
The aircraft provided an after cabin for two radar operators.
labels: where the frame of reference is within the craft
